<HEADLINE>
That's not an infield fly?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> Duwop &lt;tut...@hotmail.com&gt; </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-08-26T20:06:00 </POSTDATE>
Reading the paper about last night game where Barry was doubled up off
his infield pop up, they describe an infield out situation, but no
infield fly rule was invoked.

WTH?

Description was man on first, Barry popped up and moseyed slowly up
towards first base. The &quot;heady&quot; shortstop let the ball fall, picked it
up, forcing the man at second and then threw Barry out at first.

Why wasn't this an infield fly? Or was the description totally wrong?
It has to be.

D
