The infield fly rule pertains only when there is a force at third base
as well as second. When there's only a runner on first, the batter
should be able to &quot;beat out&quot; an intentionally dropped popup while the
defensive team gets the force play. Of course the batter has to leave
the batter's box in order to do that.
